{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-changelog-js","path":"/changelog/2017/november","result":{"data":{"markdownRemark":{"html":"<h3 id=\"inline-image-and-attachments-on-the-security-page\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#inline-image-and-attachments-on-the-security-page\" aria-label=\"inline image and attachments on the security page permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Inline Image and Attachments on the Security Page</h3>\n<p>We now enable you to attach pictures and other files to your policy. Simply go to your program's <b>Settings > Policy</b> and there will be a field where you can upload your files. We've got a nice giph on ours. <a href=\"https://hackerone.com/security\">Check it out</a>.\n<span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 500px; \"\n    >\n      <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 52%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        alt=\"nov_2017\"\n        title=\"nov_2017\"\n        src=\"/static/e5f8bc1b9023e09bc8da463a7e87d5e2/0b533/nov_2017.png\"\n        srcset=\"/static/e5f8bc1b9023e09bc8da463a7e87d5e2/fac75/nov_2017.png 125w,\n/static/e5f8bc1b9023e09bc8da463a7e87d5e2/63868/nov_2017.png 250w,\n/static/e5f8bc1b9023e09bc8da463a7e87d